    "media:imagetext": "VIEWING ONE OF THE CLIPPER SHIPS WITH\nSAN FRANCISCO-OAKLAND\nBAY\nBRIDGE\nIN BACKGROUND\nEvery Wednesday afternoon one of the big Pan Ameri-\nFlying Clippers heads\nout\nWestward over\nte Guiden Gate. Each Tuesday morning another Clipper\npasses Dastward toward the seaplane base at\nAlameda.\nOpened to passenger travel in October, 1936, these ships\nnamed\nthe\nPhilippine\nChina Clipper,\nHawaii\nClipper,\nand the\nClipper make 8200-mile journey to Manila,\nby way of Honolulu, in 60 flying hours.\nNo. 28\nFOR CORRESPONDENCE\nPUB. BY J. C. BARDELL SAN FRANCE\nPOST CARD\nTHIS SPACE FOR ADDRESS ONLY\nPLACE\nONE CENT\nSTAMP\nHERE",
